verses.text_plain: Surely there is a vein for the silver, and a place for gold where they fine it.
verses.verse_html:
1Surely there is a vein for the silver, and a place for gold where they fine it. ▼
▼ vein: or, mine

verses.text_plain: Iron is taken out of the earth, and brass is molten out of the stone.
verses.verse_html:
2Iron is taken out of the earth, and brass is molten out of the stone. ▼
▼ earth: or, dust

verses.text_plain: He setteth an end to darkness, and searcheth out all perfection: the stones of darkness, and the shadow of death.
verses.verse_html: 3He setteth an end to darkness, and searcheth out all perfection: the stones of darkness, and the shadow of death.

verses.text_plain: The flood breaketh out from the inhabitant; even the waters forgotten of the foot: they are dried up, they are gone away from men.
verses.verse_html: 4The flood breaketh out from the inhabitant; even the waters forgotten of the foot: they are dried up, they are gone away from men.

verses.text_plain: As for the earth, out of it cometh bread: and under it is turned up as it were fire.
verses.verse_html: 5As for the earth, out of it cometh bread: and under it is turned up as it were fire.

tokens.text: and under it is turned up

verses.text_plain: The stones of it are the place of sapphires: and it hath dust of gold.
verses.verse_html:
6The stones of it are the place of sapphires: and it hath dust of gold. ▼
▼ dust…: or, gold ore

footnotes.body_html: ▼ dust…: or, gold ore

verses.text_plain: There is a path which no fowl knoweth, and which the vulture’s eye hath not seen:
verses.verse_html: 7There is a path which no fowl knoweth, and which the vulture’s eye hath not seen:

verses.text_plain: The lion’s whelps have not trodden it, nor the fierce lion passed by it.
verses.verse_html: 8The lion’s whelps have not trodden it, nor the fierce lion passed by it.

verses.text_plain: He putteth forth his hand upon the rock; he overturneth the mountains by the roots.
verses.verse_html:
9He putteth forth his hand upon the rock; he overturneth the mountains by the roots. ▼
▼ rock: or, flint

verses.text_plain: He cutteth out rivers among the rocks; and his eye seeth every precious thing.
verses.verse_html: 10He cutteth out rivers among the rocks; and his eye seeth every precious thing.

verses.text_plain: He bindeth the floods from overflowing; and the thing that is hid bringeth he forth to light.
verses.verse_html:
11He bindeth the floods from overflowing; and the thing that is hid bringeth he forth to light. ▼
▼ overflowing: Heb. weeping

verses.text_plain: But where shall wisdom be found? and where is the place of understanding?
verses.verse_html: 12But where shall wisdom be found? and where is the place of understanding?

verses.text_plain: Man knoweth not the price thereof; neither is it found in the land of the living.
verses.verse_html: 13Man knoweth not the price thereof; neither is it found in the land of the living.

verses.text_plain: The depth saith, It is not in me: and the sea saith, It is not with me.
verses.verse_html: 14The depth saith, It is not in me: and the sea saith, It is not with me.

tokens.text: not in me: and the sea

verses.text_plain: It cannot be gotten for gold, neither shall silver be weighed for the price thereof.
verses.verse_html:
15It cannot be gotten for gold, neither shall silver be weighed for the price thereof. ▼
▼ It…: Heb. Fine gold shall not be given for it

footnotes.body_text: ▼ It…: Heb. Fine gold shall not be given for it
footnotes.body_html: ▼ It…: Heb. Fine gold shall not be given for it

verses.text_plain: It cannot be valued with the gold of Ophir, with the precious onyx, or the sapphire.
verses.verse_html: 16It cannot be valued with the gold of Ophir, with the precious onyx, or the sapphire.

verses.text_plain: The gold and the crystal cannot equal it: and the exchange of it shall not be for jewels of fine gold.
verses.verse_html:
17The gold and the crystal cannot equal it: and the exchange of it shall not be for jewels of fine gold. ▼
▼ jewels…: or, vessels of

footnotes.body_html: ▼ jewels…: or, vessels of

verses.text_plain: No mention shall be made of coral, or of pearls: for the price of wisdom is above rubies.
verses.verse_html:
18No mention shall be made of coral, or of pearls: for the price of wisdom is above rubies. ▼
▼ coral: or, Ramoth

verses.text_plain: The topaz of Ethiopia shall not equal it, neither shall it be valued with pure gold.
verses.verse_html: 19The topaz of Ethiopia shall not equal it, neither shall it be valued with pure gold.

tokens.text: it, neither shall it be valued

verses.text_plain: Whence then cometh wisdom? and where is the place of understanding?
verses.verse_html: 20Whence then cometh wisdom? and where is the place of understanding?

verses.text_plain: Seeing it is hid from the eyes of all living, and kept close from the fowls of the air.
verses.verse_html:
21Seeing it is hid from the eyes of all living, and kept close from the fowls of the air. ▼
▼ air: or, heaven

verses.text_plain: Destruction and death say, We have heard the fame thereof with our ears.
verses.verse_html: 22Destruction and death say, We have heard the fame thereof with our ears.

verses.text_plain: God understandeth the way thereof, and he knoweth the place thereof.
verses.verse_html: 23God understandeth the way thereof, and he knoweth the place thereof.

verses.text_plain: For he looketh to the ends of the earth, and seeth under the whole heaven;
verses.verse_html: 24For he looketh to the ends of the earth, and seeth under the whole heaven;

verses.text_plain: To make the weight for the winds; and he weigheth the waters by measure.
verses.verse_html: 25To make the weight for the winds; and he weigheth the waters by measure.

verses.text_plain: When he made a decree for the rain, and a way for the lightning of the thunder:
verses.verse_html: 26When he made a decree for the rain, and a way for the lightning of the thunder:

verses.text_plain: Then did he see it, and declare it; he prepared it, yea, and searched it out.
verses.verse_html:
27Then did he see it, and declare it; he prepared it, yea, and searched it out. ▼
▼ declare…: or, number it

tokens.text: it, yea, and searched it out

footnotes.body_html: ▼ declare…: or, number it

verses.text_plain: And unto man he said, Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom; and to depart from evil is understanding.
verses.verse_html: 28And unto man he said, Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom; and to depart from evil is understanding.
